These mirages typically appear on the horizon and can make objects seem misplaced, distorted, or even floating. Such incidents have been recorded on several occasions around the world. When these conditions are met, the phenomenon can create a rainbow-like effect that is spread horizontally across the sky.
Although I cannot verify the exact location where this image was taken, the phenomenon itself is real and can occur in various places around the world, including Idaho, when the atmospheric conditions are right. Therefore, it is plausible that this photograph could show a "fire rainbow" over Idaho.
